column5: Hey! How much is gas for the boat up there? I want to know how many cases of empties I should return.
....Best take them all back for recycling anyway Roy, least before Alcan has to up production at their smelter.
Hope to be in by noon on Thursday myself.

Just got back from dropping the boat off today, highway was good, Bassmaster Mike, Slowpoke and Muskistudd were there already, folks arrived about 40 min after I left.  Sorry Roy, forgot to check how much gas was, it's 1.35 in town....glad I made it back here to fill up at 1.27  Maureen
I may make it Thursday night,if the boss is nice to us that day,otherwhys I'll be in friday before noon......Shelleys' arrival is sometime Friday........T C and see ya there....Chuck...
Will be leaving the Hammer around noon... Boss said I could have the day off  See everyone around supper time

DANG!! Change in plans here. Was to arrive  very late Friday night/early Saturday and leave Tuesday but now looks like a late Thursday arrival  and to leave Lakair Sunday. J ain't well so I have to be here Monday morning very early.
Leavin here around 5 am on Thursday. Depending on the number of stops with the youngin, we should be there no later that 3:30-4:00 pm.
Sorry to hear that Roy, hope its not too serious.  Give J a hug for me.  Joey
J's just trying to get him outta the house...

Some have already arrived at Lakair. (Lucky stiffs) I still have 4 more sleeps to go and even then, I'll have put in a 13 hour day before I fire up the Jeep. Drive safely everyone. Looking forward to meeting and re-meeting all in attendance this year.

I'm taking the boat up this morning for the folks, leaving around 9 or so, hope to be there for noon.  Will come home tonight and then head up on Wed. to trade places with my mom   Hope I have everything...gonna take Lew's advice and pick up some tire sealant, even though I have two spares ready to go...some places on that highway are not the best for changing a tire   Hoping to take the boat for a spin and maybe wet a line while I'm there  Maureen

While he hasn't made it to Lak Air yet I know that Greencoachdog hit the road Sunday making his way up here to Virginia. He should arrive here today Mon were he gets a rest and then its load up the Southern Continguency early Tuesday and start the Candian Invasion.   Art

I'm heading back up to the trailer at noon tomorrow to get the boat, spend the night, then will be heading out around 4:00 AM on Wednesday morning and arriving about 9 or so.  I normally head up on the Monday (today) but musky opener is a week late this year so no sense sitting and twiddling my thumbs for 5 days, but I'm gonna stay over into next week for a few days  Lookin forward to seeing everybody again.

We can't head up until after work on Friday, and even at that, Paul is on afternoons.  Best case scenario is we get there very early Saturday morning.  Unless of course Paul's boss gives him a break and lets him go early Friday night, but that's doubtful (hey, you never know   ).  But we are staying the whole week after that  Looking forward to seeing you all again.  Joey

We are heading up early Thursday AM, should arrive before noon all being well. Will have the lovely Barbara with me so the arrival time will depend on the stops that we have to make along the way........   Looking forward to seeing everyone again.  Y'all drive safe Art, see you there.  Roy, I know that you drive by autopilot, but be safe, I may leave the porch light on for you.  John..
Just taking care of last minute stuff and then we are away this morning...  Beans and Maribeth
I'll be there early-ish on Friday morning. I've never been before and have only met a few of you so be gentle.

Bly and I are heading out at around 1pm on Friday afternoon....should get there around the dinner hour!  Hopefully we'll catch the evening walleye pickeral (yes TJ.... walleye pickeral ) bite.  We'll be staying until Monday morning this year....cant wait to see everyone again!
Leaving to go wenesday night if all goes well
....Oh I'll be there, but not soon enough. Getting things together today and tomorrow and leaving Wednesday morning.
The south shall rise again!!!!  Ill be there thursday nite after Averys grad.
Well, at least someone in the family will have graduated eh  Love the avatar btw!!!  Joey
....Eighth wonder of the world and a DANG miracle I tell you!

Okay I just went on mapquest and for some reason i cant get the directions to lakair I know the adress and all but it just drops me in nowhere I REALLY DONT WANT TO END UP IN THE DOKIS RESERVE AGAIN any way if some one can give me directions from Oakville it would be great  Peter
Peter, just  take 400 then 69 then right at 64.
But don't forget to stop at Cleo's for some homemade jerky!!!!!!!  Joey
THANKS ROY!!!!  Joey---where is cleo.s..............hey does that mean you have been cheating all along!!!!
....One would almost think you've never been there Pete.

Hahaha, no my jerky is different than Cleo's jerky  Cleo's is right in Noelville, at the corner store beside the gas station.  Instead of turning right at Noelville to continue to Monetville, just go strait for a few meters and its on the left.  Joey
Get at least $25 worth, if you're lucky you will still have some left when you arrive at the lodge.

Just a quick note to say that all is well on Hwy 69. I drove from Bracebridge to Sudbury just yesterday. There's no construction to worry about.  Travel safely people, and most of all, have a great time.
Aw jeez, when I saw that you responded Dan I was hoping to read that you were coming this year.  I thinks its about time you and Sis made it to a Lakair G2G.  No chance?  Joey
It's on top of our "to do" list Joey. We attended Sis's daughters wedding on Lake Muskoka this past weekend. That's why we were in the area.
And she couldn't have postponed it for a weekend so you could drive by this weekend, how selfish  Well hopefully next year will be the year  Joey
